# Execution Workflow Gates

- Follow sequence: scope -> implement -> test -> docs update -> ship.
- Before coding, confirm acceptance criteria and target files/modules.
- Write a short plan before coding (scope, success criteria, touched modules, tests).
- Keep the plan updated while implementing and mark completed steps.
- Summarize changes and rationale in PR artifacts, including risks and follow-ups.
- Include or update tests whenever behavior changes.
- Run `python -m pytest -q` (full or targeted) before preparing merge.
- Keep changes incremental; avoid unrelated refactors in the same slice.
- Keep implementation simple (KISS) and favor maintainable abstractions.
- When commands/API usage change, update user-facing docs and examples.
- Document residual risks and follow-ups explicitly when work is partial.
